Created an attachment (id=5082)
The error dialog

auto-build was on.
To fix the problem I disabled autobuild, manually re-imported the 7 plug-ins
where the project information was lost and rebuilt all.

reducing severity - it's not a blocker since I can work again after restoring my
workspace.
*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of 35454 ***

Sorry Wassim I have to reopen this bug because I do not agree that this is a
duplicate for the following reasons:
1. Dejan writes in that other bug: "
The dialog you now get warns you that we cannot resolve all referenced plug-
ins. The question you are asked is if we should assume they will come later as 
projects. If you say 'yes', we resolve them as project classpath entries 
assuming that you will make these projects appear later.
"
  Did you look at the dialog picture I attached? I can only press OK and then I
am left with a workspace that I have to fix manually.
2. this did never happen for quite a while (at least we in Zurich never saw this
with plain 2.1)
- according to dev-eclipse messages code in that area has been touched exactly
for that M1 build
- others experienced the same i.e. worked until last M1 build

I assume that the (same looking) stack trace just shows the result and not the
cause for the problem.

The only changes that were made in this area prior to the M1 build is the fix 
that JDT core put in to prevent the deadlock.
Adding Philippe as cc for comment.

Can you explain why I got a different dialog than Dejan mentions in bug 35454? I
assume that having a different dialog also means that a different code is
executed in PDE (or a different exception occurred to trigger the different dialog).

The two bugs are exactly the same.  The only difference is that Philippe was 
not importing all the required plug-ins, so he got an intermediary dialog from 
PDE asking him if he wants to resolve references to the missing plug-ins as 
project references..  After his yes/no response, the operation continued and 
there were problems with deleting projects, exactly as in your situation.
It is the same piece of code that got executed.
Dani, have you encountered this problem since that one time?
